<subSubSection id="C37F6542FF9EED4A2BC9FAC3FA32FA06" box="[198,1418,1400,1427]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF9EED4A2BC9FAC3FA32FA06" blockId="8.[151,1436,1237,2036]" box="[198,1418,1400,1427]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF9EED4A2BC9FAC3FEFEFA07" bold="true" box="[198,326,1400,1426]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wing membrane hyaline with brownish stripes; gonostylus long, with strong bristles basally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6542FF9EED482BC9FA1BFC63FEC7" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF9EED4A2BC9FA1BFCA1F9CE" blockId="8.[151,1436,1237,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF9EED4A2BC9FA1BFEB5FA2F" bold="true" box="[198,269,1440,1466]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Male.</emphasis>
Body length, 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A2AB9FA1AFE62FA2E" box="[438,474,1441,1467]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="5.7">5.7</number>
–6.0 mm. Wing length, 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A29F9FA1AFCA2FA2E" box="[758,794,1441,1467]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="4.5">4.5</number>
–5.0 mm. General color dark brown. Eyes blue, facets homogenous, ocellar tubercle brown, ocelli red. Gena and clypeus brownish gray, clypeus with dark setae. Antenna dark brown; scape bare, half the length of pedicel; pedicel approximately spherical; first flagellomere spherical, shorter than pedicel (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF9EED4A2903F9A2FD3DF9A6" box="[524,645,1561,1587]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 20" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,194,1954]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[202,1392,194,1959]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 20. Chrysopilus capillosus sp. n., male holotype: 15 — Wing, 16 — Antenna, 17 — Maxillary palpus, 18 — Male Terminalia, lateral view. 19 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 20 — Terminalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177235/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A296BF9A2FD3DF9A6" box="[612,645,1561,1587]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palpus long and acuminate (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF9EED4A2F67F9A2FB67F9A6" box="[1128,1247,1561,1587]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 20" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,194,1954]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[202,1392,194,1959]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 20. Chrysopilus capillosus sp. n., male holotype: 15 — Wing, 16 — Antenna, 17 — Maxillary palpus, 18 — Male Terminalia, lateral view. 19 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 20 — Terminalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177235/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A2FB0F9A2FB67F9A6" box="[1215,1247,1561,1587]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). Proboscis and labella golden yellow. Occiput gray, with golden setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF9EED4A2BCAF9D2FD0EF8BC" blockId="8.[151,1436,1237,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Thorax dark brown, with golden setae. Halter bare, yellowish, tip dark. Coxae brownish gray, with silvery iridescent setae; femora yellowish, tibiae darker, both with golden setae. Wing membrane hyaline with brownish stripes (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF9EED4A2A12F902FE2CF946" box="[285,404,1721,1747]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 20" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,194,1954]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[202,1392,194,1959]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 20. Chrysopilus capillosus sp. n., male holotype: 15 — Wing, 16 — Antenna, 17 — Maxillary palpus, 18 — Male Terminalia, lateral view. 19 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 20 — Terminalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177235/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A2A7BF902FE2CF946" box="[372,404,1721,1747]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
); small pigmented pterostigma; R 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A282BF972FC94F942" box="[804,812,1737,1751]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A2839F972FC85F942" box="[822,829,1737,1751]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="3.0">3</number>
reaching C very far from R 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A2F88F972FB37F942" box="[1159,1167,1737,1751]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1.0">1</number>
, without distal sinuosity; R 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A2BD4F94FFF5BF897" box="[219,227,1780,1794]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="4.0">4</number>
forking with almost right angle, without short appendage, curved medially; CuA 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A2FBFF94FFB00F897" box="[1200,1208,1780,1794]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
+A 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A2FD1F94FFB5EF897" box="[1246,1254,1780,1794]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1.0">1</number>
slightly longer than r-m; crossvein m-m close to origin of M 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A29A8F8A4FD17F8B8" box="[679,687,1823,1837]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF9EED4A2BCAF881FD7DF861" blockId="8.[151,1436,1237,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Abdomen dark brown, with golden setae, mainly on tergites. Gonocoxite and gonostylus dark brown; gonostylus long, subcylindrical but distally acuminate, with short and long distal setae, and a bunch of strong basal bristles (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF9EED4A2A31F831FE54F831" box="[318,492,1930,1956]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 20" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,194,1954]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[202,1392,194,1959]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 20. Chrysopilus capillosus sp. n., male holotype: 15 — Wing, 16 — Antenna, 17 — Maxillary palpus, 18 — Male Terminalia, lateral view. 19 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 20 — Terminalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177235/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Figures 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A2A90F831FE54F831" box="[415,492,1930,1956]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="18.5" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="18.0">18–19</number>
</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long; ejaculatory apodeme not exceeding base of terminalia; ejaculatory apodeme parallel; gonocoxal apodeme slightly curved inwards (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF9EED4A28D5F809FBEBF859" box="[986,1107,1970,1996]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 20" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,194,1954]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[202,1392,194,1959]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 20. Chrysopilus capillosus sp. n., male holotype: 15 — Wing, 16 — Antenna, 17 — Maxillary palpus, 18 — Male Terminalia, lateral view. 19 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 20 — Terminalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177235/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A2F3CF809FBEBF859" box="[1075,1107,1970,1996]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
); meso-anterior incision of tergite IX short (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF9EED4A2A57F861FE77F861" box="[344,463,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 20" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[204,1391,194,1954]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[202,1392,194,1959]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 20. Chrysopilus capillosus sp. n., male holotype: 15 — Wing, 16 — Antenna, 17 — Maxillary palpus, 18 — Male Terminalia, lateral view. 19 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 20 — Terminalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177235/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9EED4A2AA1F861FE77F861" box="[430,463,2010,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus dark brown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1A6641FF9FED4B2B98F80FFB35F867" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177235/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" targetBox="[204,1391,194,1954]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF9FED4B2B98F80FFB35F867" blockId="9.[151,1435,1972,2034]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF9FED4B2B98F80FFEE5F859" bold="true" box="[151,349,1972,1996]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">FIGURES 15–20.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C654D4AFF9FED4B2A6CF80FFDEEF85E" box="[355,598,1972,1995]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Chrysopilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capillosus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF9FED4B2A6CF80FFDEEF85E" box="[355,598,1972,1995]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Chrysopilus capillosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF9FED4B2953F80FFD20F859" bold="true" box="[604,664,1972,1996]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22257A0FF9FED4B2953F80FFD20F859" box="[604,664,1972,1996]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male holotype: 15 — Wing, 16 — Antenna, 17 — Maxillary palpus, 18 — Male Terminalia, lateral view. 19 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 20 — Terminalia, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF9CED482BCAFF2CFC63FEC7" blockId="10.[151,1436,151,498]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF9CED482BCAFF2CFE9FFF24" bold="true" box="[197,295,151,177]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Female.</emphasis>
Body length, 8.0– 
<quantity id="4C9D9B2CFF9CED482906FF23FDDFFF27" box="[521,615,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
. Wing length, 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9CED482816FF23FC85FF27" box="[793,829,152,178]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="4.8">4.8</number>
–5.0 mm. Abdomen dark brown, with long golden setae on all segments. Anterior margin of sternite VIII almost rather rounded, not acuminate, hypogynial valves with five long setae (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF9CED482AEAFF53FDE5FE97" box="[485,605,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1654,1678]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,554,1630]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[192,1395,554,1630]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Chrysopilus capillosus sp. n., female paratype: 21 — Terminalia, ventral view, 22 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 23 — Genital fork (S IX), 24 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177236/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9CED482933FF53FDE5FE97" box="[572,605,232,258]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
); anterior end of genital fork slightly acuminate, distal apodeme short (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF9CED482B90FEABFEAEFEBF" box="[159,278,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1654,1678]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,554,1630]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[192,1395,554,1630]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Chrysopilus capillosus sp. n., female paratype: 21 — Terminalia, ventral view, 22 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 23 — Genital fork (S IX), 24 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177236/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9CED482BFAFEABFEAEFEBF" box="[245,278,272,298]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus two-segmented, distal segment elongated (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF9CED48287AFEABFC54FEBF" box="[885,1004,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1654,1678]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,554,1630]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[192,1395,554,1630]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Chrysopilus capillosus sp. n., female paratype: 21 — Terminalia, ventral view, 22 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 23 — Genital fork (S IX), 24 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177236/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9CED4828C3FEABFC54FEBF" box="[972,1004,272,298]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
); common spermathecal ducts short, spermathecal ducts long; spermathecae slender and oblong (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF9CED482859FE83FC75FEC7" box="[854,973,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1654,1678]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,554,1630]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[192,1395,554,1630]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Chrysopilus capillosus sp. n., female paratype: 21 — Terminalia, ventral view, 22 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 23 — Genital fork (S IX), 24 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177236/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF9CED4828A3FE83FC75FEC7" box="[940,973,312,338]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6542FF9CED482BCAFEE4FE76FE37" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF9CED482BCAFEE4FE76FE37" blockId="10.[151,1436,151,498]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF9CED482BCAFEE4FEDDFEEC" bold="true" box="[197,357,351,377]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Distribution.</emphasis>
The known distribution of this species is the Atlantic Forest areas of the State of São Paulo, from Cubatão to Boracéia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6542FF9CED482BCAFE14FDF5FE67" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF9CED482BCAFE14FDF5FE67" blockId="10.[151,1436,151,498]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF9CED482BCAFE14FEEAFE5C" bold="true" box="[197,338,431,457]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name comes from the Latin word 
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF9CED482874FE0BFC41FE5C" box="[891,1017,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName id="4C654D4AFF9CED482874FE0BFC4DFE5C" box="[891,1013,432,457]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Chrysopilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capillosus">capillosus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
for hairy, as reference to the strong bunch of bristles on male gonostylus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
